    "162 Specifically, the model generates a pair of responses to a given prompt and then selects the more suitable response based on the constitutional principles.",
    "163 This process can be enhanced using chain-of-thought prompting, whereby the model is asked to provide a step-by-step explanation of its reasoning before making a selection.",
    "164 Chain-of-thought prompting is a technique that encourages the model to break down complex problems into 157 Id. at 8.",
    "158 See Wei et al., Chain-of-Thought Prompting Elicits Reasoning in Large Language Models, ARXIV 2, https://arxiv.org/pdf/2201.11903 [ https://perma.cc/CH8F-DW4G ] (Jan. 10, 2023, 11:07 PM) (\"[L]arge language models offer the exciting prospect of in-context few-shot learning via prompting.",
    "That is, instead of finetuning a separate language model checkpoint for each new task, one can simply 'prompt' the model with a few input-output exemplars demonstrating the task."
